milia
------------------------------------------
Milia is a C++ library created to compute cosmological distances and ages in
the Friedmann-Lemaitre-Robertson-Walker metric. The luminosity distance is
computed using elliptical functions (Kantowski, Kao, Thomas 2000). The
remaining distances are computed from the luminosity distance using Hogg 1999.
The age is computed following Thomas & Kantowski 2000, using also elliptical
functions.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.10.0-1
  libgcc1-7.3.0-3
  libgsl-devel-2.3-2
  libgsl19-2.3-2
  libmilia-devel-1.0.0-1bl2
  libmilia4-1.0.0-1bl2
  libstdc++6-7.3.0-3
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.31.1-1
  gcc-core-7.3.0-3
  gcc-g++-7.3.0-3
  libtool-2.4.6-6
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://guaix.fis.ucm.es/projects/milia/wiki

Canonical download:
  https://guaix.fis.ucm.es/hg/milia

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack milia-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./milia-1.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/milia-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/milia-1.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmilia4-1.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmilia-devel-1.0.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(milia)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/milia.README
  /usr/share/doc/milia/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/milia/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/milia/README

(libmilia4)
  /usr/bin/cygmilia-4.dll

(libmilia-devel)
  /usr/include/milia/flrw.h
  /usr/include/milia/flrw_nat.h
  /usr/include/milia/metric.h
  /usr/lib/libmilia.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/milia.pc

